WEBVTT

00:22.489 --> 00:24.157 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening. I'm
Judy Woodruff.

00:24.191 --> 00:26.293 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: And I'm Hari
Sreenivasan.

00:26.326 --> 00:31.665 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Our lead tonight
is news that
we hoped we would never have to
report.

00:31.698 --> 00:38.071 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Our managing editor, my
co-anchor and dear
friend, Gwen Ifill, died earlier
today after

00:38.105 --> 00:40.974 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
an almost yearlong battle with
cancer.

00:41.008 --> 00:46.713 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
She was a supernova in a
profession loaded
with smart and talented people.
So, it's no

00:46.747 --> 00:52.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
surprise that messages of
condolence have
flooded in all afternoon from
across the journalism

00:52.920 --> 00:55.255 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and political spectrum.

00:55.289 --> 00:57.357 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
President Obama said this at the
White House:

00:57.391 --> 01:01.695 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA, President of the
United States:
Michelle and I want to offer our
deepest condolences

01:01.728 --> 01:07.935 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to Gwen Ifill's family and all
of you, her
colleagues, on her passing.

01:07.968 --> 01:12.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Gwen was a friend of ours. She
was an extraordinary
journalist. She always kept
faith with the

01:12.906 --> 01:18.312 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
fundamental responsibilities of
her profession,
asking tough questions, holding
people in

01:18.345 --> 01:23.750 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
power accountable, and defending
a strong
and free press that makes our
democracy work.

01:23.784 --> 01:28.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I always appreciated Gwen's
reporting, even
when I was at the receiving end
of one of

01:28.255 --> 01:30.691 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
her tough and thorough
interviews.

01:30.724 --> 01:35.996 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Whether she reported from a
convention floor
or from the field, whether she
sat at the

01:36.029 --> 01:41.301 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
debate moderator's table or at
the anchor's
desk, she not only informed
today's citizens,

01:41.335 --> 01:44.304 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
but she also inspired tomorrow's
journalists.

01:44.338 --> 01:48.308 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was an especially powerful
role model
for young women and girls, who
admired her

01:48.342 --> 01:53.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
integrity, her tenacity and her
intellect,
and for whom she blazed a trail
as one-half

01:53.814 --> 01:58.618 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the first all-female anchor
team on network
news.

01:58.652 --> 02:04.858 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, Gwen did her country a great
service.
Michelle and I join her family
and her colleagues

02:04.891 --> 02:09.162 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and everybody else who loved her
in remembering
her fondly today.

02:09.196 --> 02:12.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: President Obama
today at the
White House.

02:12.833 --> 02:15.002 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're devoting most of tonight's
show to Gwen.

02:15.035 --> 02:18.138 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we start with this look at
her remarkable
life.

02:18.171 --> 02:20.107 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Good evening. I'm
Gwen Ifill.

02:20.140 --> 02:25.979 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And with those
words each evening,
Americans knew they were in good
hands, Gwen

02:26.013 --> 02:27.848 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Ifill's hands.

02:27.881 --> 02:33.820 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was the heart and soul of
PBS' "NewsHour"
and "Washington Week." She was
also beloved,

02:33.854 --> 02:40.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
sister, aunt, godmother many
times over and
friend to legions.

02:40.127 --> 02:45.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The daughter of a minister, Gwen
graduated
from Simmons College in
Massachusetts, got

02:45.298 --> 02:50.604 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
her start in journalism at The
Boston Herald-American,
before moving on to The
Baltimore Evening

02:50.637 --> 02:57.978 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Sun in 1981, then to The
Washington Post,
followed by several years as a
politics reporter

02:58.011 --> 03:00.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and White House correspondent
for The New
York Times.

03:00.781 --> 03:04.985 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Even marginal
progress could be
affected by investigations in
Little Rock

03:05.018 --> 03:06.319 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and in Washington.

03:06.353 --> 03:09.790 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: She moved to
television and
NBC News in 1994.

03:09.823 --> 03:14.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: They have to find a
way to work
with this president for the next
two years

03:14.194 --> 03:15.462 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
-- Tom.

03:15.495 --> 03:18.131 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TOM BROKAW, NBC News: NBC's Gwen
Ifill on
Capitol Hill tonight.

03:18.165 --> 03:24.704 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Then, in October
1999, she
came to PBS to host "Washington
Week," the

03:24.738 --> 03:26.506 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
long-running political
roundtable...

03:26.540 --> 03:28.275 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Good evening.

03:28.308 --> 03:32.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: ... and to become
senior correspondent
on "The NewsHour With Jim
Lehrer."

03:32.579 --> 03:36.183 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JIM LEHRER: And to our new
senior correspondent,
Gwen Ifill, welcome, Gwen.

03:36.216 --> 03:37.784 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: Thanks, Jim.

03:37.818 --> 03:41.521 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, for a preview of the
Supreme Court's
1999 term...

03:41.555 --> 03:43.857 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How would you prioritize the
needs at the
border right now?

03:43.890 --> 03:50.363 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There, she added
to her lengthy
and accomplished body of work.

03:50.397 --> 03:57.037 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In 2013, Gwen and I were honored
to assume
the great responsibility, and
joy, of co-anchoring

03:57.070 --> 03:58.171 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this program.

03:58.205 --> 04:00.207 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Good evening. I'm Judy Woodruff.

04:00.240 --> 04:01.808 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: And I'm Gwen Ifill.

04:01.842 --> 04:05.479 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Those are just some of the
stories we're covering
on tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

04:05.512 --> 04:11.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On this, the
first night of
the new "PBS NewsHour," we have
a lot of news

04:11.051 --> 04:12.953 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for you.

04:12.986 --> 04:16.823 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: We also have a new
look, but Judy
and I will be bringing you the
news and analysis

04:16.857 --> 04:18.625 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
you have come to trust.

04:18.658 --> 04:23.530 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And it was that
trust, her
dedication, that was her stock
in trade. She

04:23.563 --> 04:28.735 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was the gold standard in our
business, known
for a fierce allegiance and
loyalty to her

04:28.768 --> 04:33.473 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
family, friends, and colleagues,
but also
to the facts.

04:33.507 --> 04:36.943 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Her range was limitless. Here
are some highlights.

04:36.977 --> 04:44.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: How do we as a
nation cope with
race conflict and our inability
to see each

04:44.217 --> 04:46.019 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
other?

04:46.052 --> 04:59.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Let me turn this on its head,
because when
we talk about race in this
country, we always

04:59.933 --> 05:01.835 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
talk about African-Americans,
people of color.

05:01.868 --> 05:04.271 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want to talk to you about
white people,
OK?

05:04.304 --> 05:05.672 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
MAN: White people.

05:05.705 --> 05:08.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Why don't you
mention Donald Trump
by name?

05:08.842 --> 05:12.579 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: You know, he seems
to do a good
job mentioning his own name.

05:12.612 --> 05:13.947 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

05:13.980 --> 05:18.118 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BARACK OBAMA: So, I think I will
let him do
his advertising for him.

05:18.151 --> 05:23.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Susana Flores, the
owner, is a
legal resident who tried
unsuccessfully to

05:24.024 --> 05:26.426 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
teach me how to make tortillas.

05:26.459 --> 05:35.168 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Susana's sister, Rocina
Sandoval, who works
as a waitress, is not here
legally. She could

05:35.202 --> 05:36.503 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
easily be deported.

05:36.536 --> 05:39.439 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Gwen is in Des
Moines for Iowa's
State Fair.

05:39.472 --> 05:44.077 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: This weekend, the
political yin
and yang of a crowded field all
descended

05:44.110 --> 05:47.647 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
on Iowa at once and brought it
into especially
sharp focus.

05:47.681 --> 05:51.618 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
SEN. BERNIE SANDERS (I),
Vermont: The American
people are growing extremely
unhappy with

05:51.651 --> 05:57.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
establishment politics, with
establishment
economics, and you know what
else?

05:57.057 --> 05:58.191 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
GWEN IFILL: What?

05:58.225 --> 05:59.025 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEN. BERNIE SANDERS: Even with
establishment
media.

05:59.059 --> 06:00.026 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
GWEN IFILL: No!

06:00.060 --> 06:01.828 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SEN. BERNIE SANDERS: Yeah!

06:01.861 --> 06:03.663 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: I think every single
conversation
we have had with a Republican in
this booth,

06:03.697 --> 06:06.366 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
when we asked them about these
issues, they
have always turned it back to
talking about

06:06.399 --> 06:08.168 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Hillary Clinton.

06:08.201 --> 06:14.441 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that does seem to be the
most persuasive
argument, David, that
Republicans in this

06:14.474 --> 06:16.142 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
room have.

06:16.176 --> 06:20.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Can you see a scenario right now
in which
he would step back from the
border at all

06:20.080 --> 06:22.048 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
in a way that you can trust?

06:22.082 --> 06:24.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HILLARY RODHAM CLINTON (D),
Presidential Candidate:
Well, I think you have asked
exactly the right

06:24.184 --> 06:25.919 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
question, as you often do, Gwen.

06:25.952 --> 06:28.722 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TOM BROKAW: NBC's Gwen Ifill has
our in-depth
report.

06:28.755 --> 06:32.559 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Even marginal
progress could be
affected by investigations in
Little Rock

06:32.592 --> 06:42.602 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and in Washington involving the
president,
the first lady and their
political supporters.

06:42.636 --> 06:47.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Fifty years later, though, if
King were able
to stand in that spot and look
out, what is

06:47.107 --> 06:53.046 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the legacy of that day that some
people say,
we have a black president,
everything is much

06:53.079 --> 06:55.915 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
better, and some people say, we
have so much
farther to go?

06:55.949 --> 07:01.721 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Gwen raised
questions others
wouldn't or that wouldn't even
occur to them.

07:01.755 --> 07:06.092 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Here's one example from the vice
presidential
debate she moderated in 2004.

07:06.126 --> 07:10.930 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: I want to talk to
you about AIDS,
and not about AIDS in China or
in Africa,

07:10.964 --> 07:16.036 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but AIDS right here in this
country, where
black women between the ages of
25 and 44

07:16.069 --> 07:20.040 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are 13 times more likely to die
of the disease
than their counterparts.

07:20.073 --> 07:24.978 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What should the government's
role be in helping
to end the growth of this
epidemic?

07:25.011 --> 07:29.716 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Four years later,
she sat down
with another set of candidates.

07:29.749 --> 07:34.254 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Welcome to the first
and the only
2008 vice presidential debate.

07:34.287 --> 07:39.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Throughout that
2008 campaign,
Gwen wasn't only reporting for
the "NewsHour"

07:39.259 --> 07:43.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and "Washington Week"; she was
writing about
that moment in history.

07:43.363 --> 07:49.903 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
As the nation's first
African-American president
was elected, she marked it with
"The Breakthrough,"

07:49.936 --> 07:53.873 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the story of a new generation of
black politicians.

07:53.907 --> 07:57.110 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But it wasn't just politics that
moved her.

07:57.143 --> 08:04.017 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: This is fun. Now,
this is the
way I always wanted to do the
"NewsHour."

08:04.050 --> 08:05.752 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Have a little fun.

08:05.785 --> 08:11.157 align:left position:25%,start line:73.33% size:75%
HARRY BELAFONTE,
Singer/Actor/Civil Rights
Activist: I woke up one day and
the whole

08:11.191 --> 08:14.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
world was singing "Banana Boat."
And I didn't
really understand how powerful I
was until

08:14.260 --> 08:19.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I stood before an audience of
50,000 Japanese
trying to sing Day-O.

08:19.265 --> 08:20.367 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

08:20.400 --> 08:23.236 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARRY BELAFONTE: And I was like,
yes, I have
arrived.

08:23.269 --> 08:24.938 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

08:24.971 --> 08:27.574 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Well, I would say
you have managed
over the years to sing your
song.

08:27.607 --> 08:32.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Gwen's spirit,
nourished by
her connection to her church,
was on full

08:32.212 --> 08:36.850 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
display when she sat down with
Aretha Franklin
just one year ago tomorrow.

08:36.883 --> 08:41.087 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: So, is part of you,
you know,
always going to be Reverend C.L.
Franklin's

08:41.121 --> 08:42.088 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
daughter?

08:42.122 --> 08:43.156 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ARETHA FRANKLIN, Musician:
Absolutely.

08:43.189 --> 08:44.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: I'm a preacher's
kid, too, so
I...

08:44.124 --> 08:45.458 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ARETHA FRANKLIN: I knew you --
P.K., OK.

08:45.492 --> 08:48.128 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: But I -- I am a P.K.
But I don't
sing quite like you.

08:48.161 --> 08:50.630 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ARETHA FRANKLIN: Oh, well, we
don't all sing.

08:50.663 --> 08:51.631 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

08:51.664 --> 08:52.632 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: We have other gifts.

08:52.665 --> 08:53.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ARETHA FRANKLIN: Yes, you have
other gifts.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.369 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Indeed, she did.

08:56.403 --> 09:02.075 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of her last stories was
about the new
National Museum of African
American History

09:02.108 --> 09:03.777 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
and culture.

09:03.810 --> 09:07.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: This is an amazing
place, chockful
of the expected and the
unexpected.

09:07.814 --> 09:12.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Recently, Gwen
talked about
her love for the "NewsHour" and
what it means

09:13.019 --> 09:14.654 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in today's world:

09:14.687 --> 09:19.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: We occupy a role
that we know
they appreciate. They tell us
this.

09:19.359 --> 09:24.998 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it's not too much to tell
them back how
much we love them back. There is
-- the world

09:25.031 --> 09:28.134 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
is split into a million
different little ways
of consuming your information.

09:28.168 --> 09:33.306 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A lot of young people say, I get
my profession
from "The Daily Show." Or a lot
of young people

09:33.339 --> 09:37.043 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
say, I only read what I see on
my phone browser.

09:37.076 --> 09:42.382 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But we have a dedicated,
committed audience
who want to know more, who want
us to dig

09:42.415 --> 09:46.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a little deeper on their behalf.
And so, if
they weren't there, if they
weren't supporting

09:46.953 --> 09:48.421 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the work we do, we couldn't
exist.

09:48.455 --> 09:53.193 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think it's kind of vital
to democracy
that we do exist.

09:53.226 --> 09:58.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Gwen touched
so many lives.
And there has been a tremendous
outpouring

09:58.131 --> 09:59.899 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of remembrances today.

09:59.933 --> 10:02.135 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Attorney General Loretta Lynch
had this to
