achievement never got away from
her.

20:33.833 --> 20:41.073 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And she understood what people
went through.
And she was very helpful in
letting other

20:41.107 --> 20:46.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
young journalists know her
story. And she
brought people together. I mean,
many of the

20:46.645 --> 20:54.653 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
panelists know that she had a
really well-received
open house every New Year's Day.

20:54.687 --> 20:58.824 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I watched over the years how
that open
house got bigger and bigger, and
because she

20:58.858 --> 21:03.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
let more and more people into
the circle because
she thought it was also
important to bring

21:03.295 --> 21:09.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people together. And that was
one of the ways,
among many others, that she did
that.

21:09.201 --> 21:14.740 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Charlayne
Hunter-Gault, talk
a little bit about what she
meant to journalists

21:14.773 --> 21:17.776 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of color, to people of color.

21:17.810 --> 21:24.950 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I would be with her walking down
the street
or in a restaurant or at an
airport. And I

21:24.984 --> 21:32.057 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
would see the immediate
connection that she
had with all people, but there
was -- of course,

21:32.091 --> 21:35.327 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
because she had fans across all
the spectrums.

21:35.361 --> 21:41.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there was a connection for
her in the
African-American community that
was really

21:41.100 --> 21:42.401 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
-- it was really remarkable.

21:42.434 --> 21:44.336 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Well,
absolutely.

21:44.370 --> 21:49.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I remember, when I spoke at
the National
Press Club when she was honored
there with

21:49.074 --> 21:55.014 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
their highest award, I talked
about how she
reminded me a little bit of
Viola Davis, because,

21:55.047 --> 22:00.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
when she went through, there
weren't a whole
lot of women even then, when she
began to

22:00.986 --> 22:05.491 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
achieve national recognition and
status.

22:05.524 --> 22:11.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And she would look across that
line, like
Viola Davis said, and reach out
to bring others

22:11.664 --> 22:17.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
in. So, she inspired those she
met. But she
also inspired those just by her
appearance

22:17.136 --> 22:23.309 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and by her competence and her
extraordinary
capacity to do all the things
that you have

22:23.342 --> 22:27.346 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
heard all of her colleagues, old
and new,
talk about.

22:27.379 --> 22:31.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The other thing about Gwen was,
they say that
she could give you a look. And
that was true.

22:31.517 --> 22:32.718 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

22:32.751 --> 22:33.752 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: But she
was not full
of herself.

22:33.786 --> 22:35.554 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: No.

22:35.588 --> 22:37.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: I mean,
we -- the
last time -- and I'm so glad I
had this moment

22:37.723 --> 22:43.062 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with her on Martha's Vineyard
this past summer,
with Michele Norris, the NPR
correspondent.

22:43.095 --> 22:50.069 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The three of us were at dinner.
And she just
sat back and let us yammer and
talk and chat.

22:50.102 --> 22:53.405 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we would say something, and
she would
say, "Oh, I didn't know that."
And she would

22:53.439 --> 22:57.109 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pick up a pen and start writing
it down to
remind herself to look at that.

22:57.142 --> 23:00.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we were talking about
something else,
and she went right on her phone
and said:

23:00.579 --> 23:03.549 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"No, that's not right. It was
such and such
and such a thing."

23:03.582 --> 23:11.390 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But she was humble, even as she
presented
this very strong and powerful
person. So,

23:11.423 --> 23:18.063 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think that what young
African-American people
saw in her was what they could
be. And it

23:18.097 --> 23:22.635 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was a wonderful. And I could see
what I could
be, even being older than she.

23:22.668 --> 23:24.403 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

23:24.436 --> 23:27.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: So, I'm
just saying
that she appealed to all
generations in the

23:27.573 --> 23:29.341 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
most wonderful way.

23:29.375 --> 23:32.711 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: John
Dickerson, she also
seemed to be a journalist that
was willing

23:32.745 --> 23:34.480 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to continue learning.

23:34.513 --> 23:38.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, she didn't take to
Twitter quickly,
but, once she got in, she was
in, and the

23:38.617 --> 23:39.585 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
world knew about it.

23:39.618 --> 23:41.387 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

23:41.420 --> 23:44.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DICKERSON: Well, she had to
be somewhere
to tell everybody about
"Hamilton" and every

23:44.056 --> 23:45.924 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
song that she was listening to.

23:45.958 --> 23:47.159 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

23:47.192 --> 23:48.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I was waiting for
somebody
to bring that up.

23:48.093 --> 23:49.828 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

23:49.862 --> 23:53.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN DICKERSON: Well, I felt as
though I had
to do it for Gwen. Talk about a
woman who

23:53.432 --> 23:56.135 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
didn't throw away her shot.

23:56.168 --> 24:02.041 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was an enthusiast, you know?
She was an
enthusiast about Twitter,
although skeptical

24:02.074 --> 24:07.680 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
at first, you know, because --
in part because
I think she probably thought it
was just a

24:07.713 --> 24:13.919 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
place for people to just kind of
toss off
opinions that might not be
considered.

24:13.952 --> 24:19.325 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But then, when she took to it
with her normal
enthusiasm -- and that
enthusiasm, as we said,

24:19.358 --> 24:26.598 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
often was in the form of either
glory to "Hamilton"
or lyrics from it -- it was just
a perfect

24:26.632 --> 24:29.201 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
venue for her enthusiasm to come
through.

24:29.234 --> 24:34.873 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that's what I think about
all today, was
just her enthusiasm in all of
its different

24:34.907 --> 24:38.911 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
forms. And, certainly, in the
new world of
social media, it was there, too.

24:38.944 --> 24:43.382 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Kevin Merida, I
want to come
back to you on, you know, we --
all of us

24:43.415 --> 24:48.253 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
lived through journalism
changing rapidly.
Twitter is a part of that.

24:48.287 --> 24:53.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
How did you see Gwen adapting as
journalism
changed right in front of all
our eyes?

24:53.726 --> 24:58.430 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KEVIN MERIDA: Well, she grasped
it like she
did everything. It was a
challenge and something

24:58.464 --> 25:00.265 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
interesting for her.

25:00.299 --> 25:03.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I would see, sometimes, I
would tweet
something, and then she would
come back with

25:03.135 --> 25:06.472 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
