25:22.020 --> 25:27.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I remember writing that, you
know, early
on. And she sent, "I love you,
Kevin Merida,"

25:27.426 --> 25:28.394 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you know?

25:28.427 --> 25:29.795 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(LAUGHTER)

25:29.828 --> 25:31.930 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
KEVIN MERIDA: And it was just a
little funny,
you know, rejoinder.

25:31.964 --> 25:39.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I think that she was so
accomplished and
so well-regarded by so many
other people,

25:39.571 --> 25:43.308 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but, for her, she always wanted
to keep learning
and getting better.

25:43.342 --> 25:49.615 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, as Charlayne said and
others, she was
willing to learn from others.
She just soaked

25:49.648 --> 25:54.620 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
up -- the passion in her for
knowledge was
just amazing.

25:54.653 --> 26:00.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: And she was that
rare competitor
in -- at least in Washington,
that wasn't

26:00.826 --> 26:02.594 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
moving ahead by putting somebody
else down.

26:02.628 --> 26:04.530 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KEVIN MERIDA: That's right.

26:04.563 --> 26:07.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: If she was going to
get the moderator
job, if she was going to get the
big interview,

26:07.199 --> 26:11.336 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
she was going to get it because
of the work
that she did, not because she
made somebody

26:11.370 --> 26:15.274 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
else feel bad or pushed them
down in any way.

26:15.307 --> 26:22.815 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that, especially in this
town, is a remarkable
-- first of all, it's been a
remarkable gift

26:22.848 --> 26:26.051 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for so many of us, but it's not
something
that you see very often.

26:26.084 --> 26:27.986 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
KEVIN MERIDA: So incredibly
classy.

26:28.020 --> 26:32.591 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I would just say,
in our final
minute with you and Amy Walter
and John Dickerson,

26:32.624 --> 26:38.263 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I know Gwen really hated, when I
talked to
her, missing covering the end of
this amazing,

26:38.297 --> 26:43.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
one-of-a-kind presidential
campaign. That
was hard for her to miss it.

26:43.135 --> 26:47.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: To not be -- to not
spend an election
night -- I have spent a lot of
election nights

26:47.172 --> 26:48.140 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
with Gwen Ifill.

26:48.173 --> 26:49.741 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: John?

26:49.775 --> 26:51.944 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: Judy,
can I just -- can
I just say one final thing?

26:51.977 --> 26:53.212 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Fifteen seconds.
Sure.

26:53.245 --> 26:55.547 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
CHARLAYNE HUNTER-GAULT: And I
hope -- I hope
I don't cry.

26:55.581 --> 27:01.053 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I saw her on the air one
night, and she
looked so amazing. And, at 10:00
at night,

27:01.086 --> 27:06.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I couldn't help but write to
her. And that's
when she wrote me back and told
me how -- what

27:06.124 --> 27:07.926 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
she had been going through.

27:07.960 --> 27:12.464 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think that's another thing
that we should
absolutely think so highly of
her, because

27:12.498 --> 27:19.671 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
she worked through all of her
illness without
letting on to anyone about what
was going

27:19.705 --> 27:21.440 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on.

27:21.473 --> 27:23.509 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The "NewsHour" would say, she's
away, and
everybody thought she was away
working. And

27:23.542 --> 27:27.179 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
she was suffering mightily. And
she bore it
with such grace.

27:27.212 --> 27:28.881 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Yes.

27:28.914 --> 27:30.582 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Thank you,
Charlayne.

27:30.616 --> 27:32.351 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Thank you,
Charlayne.

27:32.384 --> 27:36.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Absolutely, she was a pillar of
strength for
everybody out there and for all
of us here

27:36.121 --> 27:37.890 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
at the "NewsHour."

27:37.923 --> 27:43.562 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Charlayne Hunter-Gault, Kevin
Merida, John
Dickerson, Amy Walter right
here, we thank

27:43.595 --> 27:45.631 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
you all.

27:45.664 --> 27:52.704 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
KEVIN MERIDA: Thank you.

27:52.738 --> 28:01.580 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
AMY WALTER: Thank you, Judy.

28:01.613 --> 28:09.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Now more
remembrances of
Gwen from Rick Berke. He's
executive editor

28:09.454 --> 28:15.594 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
